title: For Sale:  2015 WASR for sale
postcontent: I have a 2015 Romanian WASR for sale.  I've put around 400 rounds through it, and the only failures I had occurred after I first got it.  It would have on average one failure per magazine, which was a failure to extract.  The extractor looked worn, so I got a Polish extractor from Apex and it has not had a single failure since then.  As you can see, it has a full set of Magpul furniture on it, and has been painted in a woodland color, with Krylon camo paint.  It's actually pretty durable, but I did it with spray paint so that it can always be touched up or taken off all together.  I get compliments on the paint job all the time, so yes, it looks good.  I will include two Magpul magazines (gen 1s) with it that are also painted to match the gun. I have painted the back of the front sight in bright orange so that it can better be used as the "poor man's eotech" as Rob from AKOU says, meaning that it works the same way a red dot sight does, in that you only have to line up the bright orange with your target.  It works great for close targets.  The muzzle brake is something I made from a barrel extension from CNC Warrior.  It works well, but you can always get something else if you don't like it.  Cleaning rod included.  This has the Century Rak1 trigger group, and it's very decent, I can hit a 12 inch steel plate at 300 yards with this, open sights.  The sling is NOT included.  As stated above, you will get the Magpul furniture, which includes the MOE triangle stock, the MOE handguard and the MOE foregrip. Price is $700.  I will NOT ship.  No ammo included.  Please be within an hour of Chambersburg PA, or be willing to meet me halfway.

The BKA BR 15 is one of the first models produced by Black Knight Armorers LLC. title: For Sale/Trade:  Molot VEPR 308 flat back custom AK
postcontent: What you see here is a early import, Molot VEPR chambered in 308 Winchester. Suffice it to say, this gun is far from its original configuration. I will go over the impressive list of modifications in a moment, let's talk about the base gun first. The VEPR line is based off of the original Russian RPK model. It features a robust construction, with thicker receiver and trunions. This particular model is a type II with integrated FSB/GB. It also has the more desirable, flat back receiver! This allows the use of several standard AK stamped receiver stocks, without a adapter. It also features a spring loaded firing pin, to avoid slam fires common with commercial ammunition and free floated pins. This particular gun is still in unfired condition, and has only recently been finish built. Made to last generations, the VEPR line is as tough as it looks! This gun as stated, is far from stock. It started life as a standard 20.5" barreled VEPR with the 2x4 wood furniture. When I say 2x4 furniture, I'm not exaggerating! It wasn't fit for this rifle. To build this exactly as shown, with the mags, expect to spend around 2700.00! Why do I say that, I'll tell you. Lantac Drakon muzzle brake (145.00), CSSPECS mags seven in total (240.00), Manticore Arms handguard unmodified (200.00), RS Regulate scope mount top and bottom (180.00), Leupold VXR-R patrol optic with Leupold QD rings (380.00), FAB Defense AK rubberized grip (30.00), LUTH-AR stock with adapter (185.00), and the gun, if you can find a NIB flat back, 800.00. Total without gunsmith labor, over 2100.00. You may ask me what gunsmith work was done. Well, for starters, I had the barrel shortened. I wanted to be around 21" with the muzzle brake. He cut, crowned, and threaded it at 19". That gives you a barrel length that's perfect for the 308 round. He then indexed the muzzle brake correctly, to the 14×1 LH thread. Next up was the scope. Many people just buy the Russian combo optics. While they are nice, there is a reason they came serial numbered to the gun. Often times, they need to be fitted to the rifles side rail to guarantee zero! Most people don't do this, and wonder why they can't zero their new optic. Enter RS Regulate. Due to their unique two peace design, you can zero the top half of the mount over the rifle! This was indeed done with a lazer alignment systeml. Also bore sighted at 50 yards to get you on paper fast. To top it off, the top half of the mount is a 1913 rail! Don't like the Leupold, simply pop it off via the QD mounts. The 1913 mount itself is still centered over the rifle! My smith also custom modified the handguard by removing the top halves of keymod, exposing the gas tube! It shaves weight, while just looking bad ass! Truly one off design. Last up is the custom two tone cerokote. It's a flat black, sniper gray mix. All of this labor wise comes out to around 320.00. With this gun you will also receive everything pictured on the gun! Seven CSSPECS steel double stack mags in total also cerokoted! Six 20 rounders and one 10 rounder. Put this all together with the endless adjustment of the LUTH-AR stock, and you have one serious rifle! The last picture is of this exact rifle in its stock form! That way, you can truly appreciate the amount of work into it! I can accept PayPal friends and family payment, or USPS money order. Have questions, please ask! I probably only scratched the surface with this description!

title: For Sale:  Original German WW II Mauser K98 Bolt Action Rifle **NUMBERS MATCHING**
postcontent:
According to Mitchell's Mausers:  "The Mitchell's Mausers Collection contains rare K98 Mausers built during WWII by the German war machine. All complete with the military proof marks and acceptance stamps, which read like a history book. The Mauser K98 is an authentic piece of History for any collector. These rifles remain first in Bolt Action Design, Strength, Reliability, Accuracy and Safety.
All K98k were issued to a German soldiers and actually used in WWII, most likely in combat. After the war, the allies took control of all of the German K98k’s. The rifles offered from Mitchell's Mausers Collection survived the war in superior condition and still work like the day they were made.
    Matching serial numbers - Original German markings - Cleaned and inspected" [could more accurately be called "arsenal refurbished"]  *Including WW II original accessories plus lots of extras - original ammo pouch, original cleaning pull through, original oiler, original screwdriver tool, official Mitchell's Mausers Letter of Provenance, english manual, reproduction bayonet, reproduction sling, and lots of extra stripper clips, AND a .30 cal ammo can with 12 boxes of 8mm Yugoslavian surplus ammo in stripper clips (180 rounds), 5 boxes of PRVI Partizan 196grain M75 sniper ammo, 1990s manufacture without stripper clips (75 rounds), plus 7 extra loaded stripper clips with a mix of surplus and sniper ammo for a total of approx. 290 rounds of good quality ammo.
The rifle has obviously been refinished although there are a few minor cosmetic blemishes and areas where the stock looks to have been repaired before refinishing, probably at the arsenal; the metal and wood finish are both in great shape; bore is pitted, with visible rifling but showing signs of significant use and age.  I have tons of pics, email for more info.
According to Mitchells: "Unfortunately, it is true  —  NAZI Mausers are sold out world wide.  Hitler’s NAZI’s were defeated seventy years ago; and the Iron Curtain fell twenty-five years ago.  Since then astute collectors have taken most all of the NAZI-marked rifles that had been stored in the old Soviet warehouses.  More recently, the Russia-Ukraine conflict cut us off from the last few NAZI rifles in Russia.  There are simply no NAZI rifles available  –  anywhere."  [Except for this one!]
The supply of these rifles has really dried up these days; Mitchell's has been sold out for a long time now, and even on gunbroker you'll be hard pressed to find one in this condition.
NOTE: I make no guarantees as to the accuracy of any information quoted from Mitchells or appearing on their Letter of Provenance.  All used firearms should be checked by a qualified gunsmith before use. CASH ONLY - NO TRADES - Serious inquiries only; No Shipping. Local sales ONLY.
